# 240-MP QML & C++ Conventions

Apply these when editing any module or shell code in this fork.

## QML views

```qml
FocusScope {
    id: itemsRoot
    property var navParams: ({})
    property var navListState: navParams.navListState || ({})
    signal navigateTo(string path, var params, var listState)
    signal goBack()
    // Escape/Backspace → goBack()
    // Sizes: root.sh, root.sw — never literal pixels
}
```

- Module router `Root.qml`: `id: moduleRoot`; only `goBack()` leaves the module.
- `moduleName` / `moduleIcon` from `appCore.get_module_info("com.240mp.<id>")`.
- List views restore `currentIndex` from `navListState` on `Component.onCompleted`.

## C++ backends

- `Q_INVOKABLE` for QML-called slots; `signals:` for async results.
- Persist state via JSON in the data dir; read settings in the constructor.
- `registerModule` auto-wires (exact signatures): `dynamicOptionsReady`, `authStateChanged`, `onSettingChanged`.

## Config

```qml
appCore.get_setting("com.240mp.iptv_tuner", "m3u_url")
appCore.save_setting("com.240mp.iptv_tuner", "guide_mode", "passive")
```

## Scope discipline in this fork

Prefer module-only diffs. Touch `AppCore`, `MpvController`, or `Main.qml` only when the IPTV feature genuinely needs shell support (e.g. URL setting type, mpv zoom flags).
